    "methodology": "Drug poisoning deaths are based on ONS registrations using ICD-10 codes for drug-related deaths, covering both legal and illegal substances. Treatment numbers are drawn from the National Drug Treatment Monitoring System (NDTMS), published by OHID. Funding per head is calculated from local authority public health grant expenditure on substance misuse services, divided by mid-year population estimates.",
